</div>

<div class= "ingredients_header">
<section> Ingredients </section>
</div>


<ul> 
    <div class= "ingridients"> 
    <li>6 eggs </li>
    <li>120 gr of sugar </li>
    <li>400 gr of philadelphia cheese </li>
    <li>Cocoa powder </li>
    <li>400 gr of Templates (Lady Fingers)</li>
    <li>1/2 liter of Black Coffee </li>
    <li> A piece of grated dark chocolate (optional) for the last layer after cocoa </li>
    
    </div>
</ul>

<p class= "directions_header">Directions</p>
<ol> 
    <div class= "directions">
    <li> Separate the egg whites from the yolk of the eggs.</li>
    <li> Then put the egg whites in a  blender and set the speed to the maximum, and little by little start adding the sugar (half 60grs) until they are pretty firm.</li>
    <li> In a separate bowl, beat the yolks and half the sugar (60 gr) with an electric mixer . Add philadelphia cheese and mix evenly. </li>
    <li> Add the egg whites slowly and delicately and mix until it is snow like. This is your “philadelphia cream”.</li>
    <li>  Make coffee </li>
    <li> Soak the lady fingers in the coffee quickly </li>
    <li> Take the fingers and put into a pan. This will act like the first layer of the Tiramisu.  </li>
    <li> Add a generous layer of the philadelphia cream on top of the lady fingers.  </li>
    <li> Dust some cocoa powder on top of the cream.  </li>
    <li> Repeat steps 7-9.  </li>
    <li>On the last layer grate some dark chocolate to insead of a layer of cacao powder.</li>
    <li>Put the tiramisu in the fridge for about three hours or until when your guest or your Kraving kicks in!</li>
    
    </div>
</ol>


<h1 class= "tips"> Insider's Secrets </h1>
<ul> 
    <div class="tiptext">
    <li class="1"> When you separate the egg whites from the yolk make sure that they is no leftover yolk. Also keep the egg whites in a clean bowl without any residue of water or other substances, treat them as the temperamental queens they are.</li>
    <li class="1"> When you make the coffee make sure you make it concentrated (even if you are not a coffee fan) because otherwise the lady fingers will taste like if they had been soaked in water instead of coffee. </li>
     <li class="1">Sweeten the coffee at least a little otherwise it will be really bitter. The amount of sugar is up to your preference. </li>
     <li class="1">The best Ladyfingers to get are from Whole Foods because they are the ones that absorb the most without falling apart.</li>
     <li class="1">When you dip the Lady fingers into the coffee don’t let them soak for minutes. It has to be quick so that the fingers don’t fall apart.</li>
     <li class="1">Pro Tip: Add about 2 more spoon fulls of the philadelphia cream when making the layers to balance the cream to sweetness ratio.</li>
    </div>
</ul>

